"3213","and</P>"
"3214","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3215","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>WHEREAS, the Advisory Agreement"
"3216","between the Trust, on behalf of the Fund, and the Adviser has been terminated by the assignment of the Advisory Agreement;</P>"
"3217","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3218","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>WHEREAS, Rule 15a-4 under"
"3219","the 1940 Act (&ldquo;Rule 15a-4&rdquo;) permits an interim investment advisory agreement subject to and in conformity the terms"
"3220","of such rule; and</P>"
"3221","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3222","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>WHEREAS, the Trust seeks"
"3223","to retain the Adviser, pursuant to Rule 15a-4, to furnish investment advisory and other services to the Trust for the Fund;</P>"
"3224","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3225","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration"
"3226","of the mutual covenants and agreements contained in this Agreement and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and"
"3227","adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged, the Adviser and the Trust agree as follows:</P>"
"3228","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3229","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>The James Advantage Funds"
"3230","(the &ldquo;Trust&rdquo;) herewith confirms our agreement with you.</P>"
"3231","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3232","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>The Trust has been organized"
"3233","to engage in the business of an investment company. The Trust currently offers several series of shares to investors, one of which"
"3234","is the James Mid Cap Fund (the &ldquo;Fund&rdquo;).</P>"
"3235","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3236","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>You have been selected"
"3237","to act as the sole investment adviser of the Fund and to provide certain other services, as more fully set forth below, and you"
"3238","are willing to act as such investment adviser and to perform such services under the terms and conditions hereinafter set forth."
"3239","Accordingly, the Trust agrees with you as follows upon the date of the execution of this Agreement.</P>"
"3240","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3241","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>ADVISORY"
"3242","SERVICES</U></P>"
"3243","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3244","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>You will regularly provide"
"3245","the Fund with such investment advice as you in your discretion deem advisable and will furnish a continuous investment program"
"3246","for the Fund consistent with the Fund&lsquo;s investment objectives and policies. You will determine the securities to be purchased"
"3247","for the Fund, the portfolio securities to be held or sold by the Fund and the portion of the Fund&rsquo;s assets to be held uninvested,"
"3248","subject always to the Fund&lsquo;s investment objectives, policies and restrictions, as each of the same shall be from time to"
"3249","time in effect, and subject further to such policies and instructions as the Board of Trustees of the Trust (the &ldquo;Board&rdquo;)"
"3250","may from time to time establish. You will advise and assist the officers of the Trust in taking such steps as are necessary or"
"3251","appropriate to carry out the decisions of the Board and the appropriate committees of the Board regarding the conduct of the business"
"3252","of the Fund.</P>"
"3253","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3254","<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 1 -->"
"3255","    <DIV STYLE=margin-bottom: 6pt><P STYLE=margin-top: 0pt; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0pt; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif></P></DIV>"
"3256","    <DIV STYLE=page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt><P STYLE=margin: 0pt>&nbsp;</P></DIV>"
"3257","    <!-- Field: /Page -->"
"3258","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify></P>"
"3259","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>ALLOCATION"
"3260","OF CHARGES AND EXPENSES</U></P>"
"3261","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3262","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>You will pay all organizational,"
"3263","offering and operating expenses (other than expenses specifically assumed by the Fund) of the Fund, including the compensation"
"3264","and expenses of any employees of the Fund and of any other persons rendering any services to the Fund; clerical and shareholder"
"3265","service staff salaries; office space and other office expenses; fees and expenses incurred by the Fund in connection with membership"
"3266","in investment company organizations; legal, auditing and accounting expenses; expenses of registering shares under federal and"
"3267","state securities laws; insurance expenses; fees and expenses of the custodian, transfer agent, dividend disbursing agent, shareholder"
"3268","service agent, plan agent, administrator, accounting and pricing services agent and underwriter of the Fund; expenses, including"
"3269","clerical expenses, of issue, sale redemption or repurchase of shares of the Fund; the cost of preparing and distributing reports"
"3270","and notices to shareholders, the cost of printing or preparing prospectuses and statements of additional information for delivery"
"3271","to the Fund&rsquo;s current shareholders; the cost of printing or preparing stock certificates or any other documents, statements"
"3272","or reports to shareholders; expenses of shareholders&rsquo; meetings and proxy solicitations; and all other operating expenses"
"3273","not specifically assumed by the Fund.</P>"
"3274","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3275","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>The Fund will pay all brokerage"
"3276","fees and commissions, taxes, interest, fees and expenses of the non-interested person trustees and such extraordinary or non-recurring"
"3277","expenses as may arise, including litigation to which the Fund may be a party and indemnification of the Trust&rsquo;s trustees"
"3278","and officers with respect thereto. The Fund will pay all expenses which may be incurred pursuant to the Fund&rsquo;s Rule 12b-1"
"3279","Distribution Plan (the &ldquo;12b-1 Expenses&rdquo;). You may obtain reimbursement from the Fund, at such time or times as you"
"3280","may determine in your sole discretion, for any of the expenses advanced by you, which the Fund is obligated to pay, and such reimbursement"
"3281","shall not be considered to be part of your compensation pursuant to this Agreement.</P>"
"3282","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3283","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>COMPENSATION"
"3284","OF THE ADVISER</U></P>"
"3285","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3286","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>For all of the services"
"3287","to be rendered and payments to be made as provided in this Agreement, as of the last business day of each month, the Fund will"
"3288","pay you a fee: (a) (i) at the annual rate of 1.25% of the average value of its daily net assets for assets up to and including"
"3289","$500 million, (ii) at the annual rate of 1.20% of the average value of its daily net assets for assets from $500 million up to"
"3290","and including $1 billion, (iii) at the annual rate of 1.15% of the average value of its daily net assets for assets from $1 billion"
"3291","up to and including $2 billion, and (iv) at the annual rate of 1.10% of the average value of its daily net assets for assets over"
"3292","$2 billion; minus (b) the fees and expenses of the non-interested person trustees incurred by the Fund.</P>"
"3293","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3294","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>The average value of the"
"3295","daily net assets of the Fund shall be determined pursuant to the applicable provisions of the Declaration of Trust of the Trust"
"3296","or a resolution of the Board, if required. If, pursuant to such provisions, the determination of net asset value of the fund is"
"3297","suspended for any particular business day, then for the purposes of this paragraph, the value of the net assets of the Fund as"
"3298","last determined shall be deemed to be the value of the net assets as of the close of the business day, or as of such other time"
"3299","as the value of the Fund&rsquo;s net assets may lawfully be determined, on that day. If the determination of the net asset value"
"3300","of the Fund has been suspended for a period including such month, your compensation payable at the end of such month shall be computed"
"3301","on the basis of the value of the net assets of the Fund as last determined (whether during or prior to such month).</P>"
"3302","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3303","<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 2; Options: NewSection; Value: 2 -->"
"3304","    <DIV STYLE=margin-bottom: 6pt><P STYLE=margin-top: 0pt; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0pt; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->2<!-- Field: /Sequence -->&nbsp;</P></DIV>"
"3305","    <DIV STYLE=page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt><P STYLE=margin: 0pt>&nbsp;</P></DIV>"
"3306","    <!-- Field: /Page -->"
"3307","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify></P>"
"3308","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>EXECUTION"
"3309","OF PURCHASE AND SALE ORDERS</U></P>"
"3310","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3311","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>In connection with purchases"
"3312","or sales of portfolio securities for the account of the Fund, it is understood that you will arrange for the placing of all orders"
"3313","for the purchase and sale of portfolio securities for the account with brokers or dealers selected by you, subject to review of"
"3314","this selection by the Board from time to time. You will be responsible for the negotiation and the allocation of principal business"
"3315","and portfolio brokerage. In the selection of such brokers or dealers and the placing of such orders, you are directed at all times"
"3316","to seek for the Fund the best qualitative execution, taking into account such factors as price (including the applicable brokerage"
"3317","commission or dealer spread) the execution capability, financial responsibility and responsiveness of the broker or dealer and"
"3318","the brokerage and research services provided by the broker or dealer.</P>"
"3319","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3320","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>You should generally seek"
"3321","favorable prices and commission rates that are reasonable in relation to the benefits received. In seeking best qualitative execution,"
"3322","you are authorized to select brokers or dealers who also provide brokerage and research services (as those terms are defined in"
"3323","Section 28(e) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934) to the Fund and/or the other accounts over which you exercise investment"
"3324","discretion. You are authorized to pay a broker or dealer who provides such brokerage and research services a commission for executing"
"3325","a Fund portfolio transaction which is in excess of the amount of commission another broker or dealer would have charged for effecting"
"3326","that transaction if you determine in good faith that the amount of the commission is reasonable in relation to the value of the"
"3327","brokerage and research services provided by the executing broker or dealer. The determination may be viewed in terms of either"
"3328","a particular transaction or your overall responsibilities with respect to the Fund and to accounts over which you exercise investment"
"3329","discretion. The Fund and you understand and acknowledge that, although the information may be useful to the Fund and you, it is"
"3330","not possible to place a dollar value on such information. The Board shall periodically review the commissions paid by the Fund"
"3331","to determine if the commissions paid over representative periods of time were reasonable in relation to the benefits to the Fund.</P>"
"3332","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3333","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>Subject to the provisions"
"3334","of the Investment Company Act of 1940, as amended (the &ldquo;Act&rdquo;), and other applicable law, you, any of your affiliates"
"3335","or any affiliates of your affiliates may retain compensation in connection with effecting the Fund&rsquo;s portfolio transactions,"
"3336","including transactions effected through others. If any occasion should arise in which you give any advice to clients of yours concerning"
"3337","the shares of the Fund, you will act solely as investment counsel for such client and not in any way on behalf of the Fund. Your"
"3338","services to the Fund pursuant to this Agreement are not to be deemed to be exclusive and it is understood that you may render investment"
"3339","advice, management and other services to others, including other registered investment companies.</P>"
"3340","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3341","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>LIMITATION"
"3342","OF LIABILITY OF ADVISER</U></P>"
"3343","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3344","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>You may rely on information"
"3345","reasonably believed by you to be accurate and reliable. Except as may otherwise be required by the Act or the rules thereunder,"
"3346","neither you nor your officers, directors, employees, agents, control persons or affiliates of any thereof shall be subject to any"
"3347","liability for, or any damages, expenses or losses incurred by the Trust in connection with, any error of judgement, mistake of"
"3348","law, any act or omission connected with or arising out of any services rendered under, or payments made pursuant to, this Agreement"
"3349","or any other matter to which this Agreement relates, except by reason of willful misfeasance, bad faith or gross negligence on"
"3350","the part of any such persons in the performance of your duties under this Agreement, or by reason of reckless disregard by any"
"3351","of such persons of your obligations and duties under this Agreement.</P>"
"3352","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3353","<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 3; Value: 2 -->"
"3354","    <DIV STYLE=margin-bottom: 6pt><P STYLE=margin-top: 0pt; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0pt; font: 9pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif><!-- Field: Sequence; Type: Arabic; Name: PageNo -->3<!-- Field: /Sequence -->&nbsp;</P></DIV>"
"3355","    <DIV STYLE=page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt><P STYLE=margin: 0pt>&nbsp;</P></DIV>"
"3356","    <!-- Field: /Page -->"
"3357","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify></P>"
"3358","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>Any person, even though"
"3359","also a director, officer, employee or agent of you, who may be or become an officer, director, trustee, employee or agent of the"
"3360","Trust, shall be deemed. when rendering services to the Trust or acting on any business of the Trust (other than services or business"
"3361","in connection with your duties hereunder), to be rendering such services to or acting solely for the Trust and not as a director,"
"3362","officer, employee or agent of you, or one under your control or direction, even though paid by you.</P>"
"3363","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3364","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>DURATION"
"3365","AND TERMINATION OF THIS AGREEMENT</U></P>"
"3366","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3367","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>This Agreement shall take"
"3368","effect on the date of its execution by you, and shall remain in force for a period of one hundred and fifty (150) days from the"
"3369","date of its execution.</P>"
"3370","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3371","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>This Agreement may, on"
"3372","ten (10) days written notice, be terminated with respect to the Fund, at any time without the payment of any penalty, by the Board"
"3373","or by a vote of a majority of the outstanding voting securities of the Fund. This Agreement may also be terminated by you on sixty"
"3374","(60) days&rsquo; prior written notice to the Trust. This Agreement shall automatically terminate in the event of its assignment.</P>"
"3375","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3376","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>USE"
"3377","OF NAME</U></P>"
"3378","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3379","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>The Trust and you acknowledge"
"3380","that all rights to the name &ldquo;James Mid Cap,&rdquo; or any variation thereof, belongs to you, and that the Trust is being"
"3381","granted a limited license to use such words in its Fund name or in any class name. In the event you cease to be the adviser to"
"3382","the Fund, the Trust&rsquo;s right to use the name &ldquo;James Mid Cap,&rdquo; or any variation thereof, shall automatically cease"
"3383","on the ninetieth (90th) day following the termination of this Agreement. The right to the name may also be withdrawn by you during"
"3384","the term of this Agreement upon ninety (90) days&rsquo; written notice by you to the Trust. Nothing contained herein shall impair"
"3385","or diminish in any respect, your right to use the name &ldquo;James Mid Cap,&rdquo; or any variation thereof, in the name of, or"
"3386","in connection with, any other business enterprises with which you are or may become associated. There is no charge to the Trust"
"3387","for the right to use these names.</P>"
"3388","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3389","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>AMENDMENT"
"3390","OF THIS AGREEMENT</U></P>"
"3391","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3392","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>No provision of this Agreement"
"3393","may be changed, waived, discharged or terminated orally, and no amendment of this Agreement shall be effective until approved by"
"3394","the Board, including a majority of the trustees who are not interested persons of you or of the Trust, cast in person at a meeting"
"3395","called for the purpose of voting on such approval, and (if required under interpretations of the Act by the Securities and Exchange"
"3396","Commission) by vote of the holders of a majority of the outstanding voting securities of the series to which the amendment relates.</P>"
"3397","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3398","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>LIMITATION"
"3399","OF LIABILITY TO TRUST PROPERTY</U></P>"
"3400","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
"3401","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>The term &ldquo;James Advantage"
"3402","Funds&rdquo; means and refers to the Trustees from time to time serving under the Trust&rsquo;s Declaration of Trust as the same"
"3403","may subsequently thereto have been, or subsequently hereto be, amended. It is expressly agreed that the obligations of the Trust"
"3404","hereunder shall not be binding upon any of the trustees, shareholders, nominees, officers, agents or employees of the Trust personally,"
"3405","but bind only the trust property of the Trust, as provided in the Declaration of Trust of the Trust. The execution and delivery"
"3406","of this Agreement have been authorized by the trustees and shareholders of the Trust and signed by officers of the Trust, acting"
"3407","as such, and neither such authorization by such trustees and shareholders nor such execution and delivery by such officers shall"
"3408","be deemed to have been made by any of them individually or to impose any liability on any of them personally, but shall bind only"
"3409","the trust property of the Trust as provided in its Declaration of Trust. A copy of the Agreement and Declaration of Trust of the"
"3410","Trust is on file with the Secretary of the State of Ohio.</P>"
"3411","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.5in>&nbsp;</P>"
